---
3md: 1.0
axis: depth
title: Voxel Heart - 3D Sculpture
sculptor: CorvidLabs
shape: heart
slices: "7"
render: stack the grid planes in blend mode to see the solid 3D heart
---
A 3D voxel sculpture. Each plane is one depth slice of a solid heart.
Viewed flat, each slice is a cross section. Stack all seven grids in the
viewer's blend mode and they fuse into a recognizable three dimensional heart:
a thin tip at the back, swelling to the full two-lobed body in the middle,
then tapering back to a thin front. The grids share an identical 16 wide by
12 tall frame so the voxels align cleanly across depth.

Scrub from [[z=0|the back tip]] to [[z=6|the front tip]], or blend them all.

@plane z=0 label="slice 0 - back tip" cross="smallest core"
# Depth slice 0 (rear)

The deepest, smallest slice. Just the inner core of the two lobes.

```
................
................
................
.....o....o.....
.....o....o.....
.....o....o.....
......o..o......
......o..o......
.......oo.......
................
................
................
```

